properties.desc: You find yourself in a town of miners. It seems to be an outpost here more than anything.
You enter the back room, and see what looks like a primitive office.
You find yourself in an enclosed, dead forest. You wonder how the trees grew inside a cave.
You find yourself in an enclosed, dead forest. You wonder how the trees grew inside a cave.
You are whisked through the strange, ancient artifact disguised as a rug and into a mysterious library.
You see a table and chairs nearby, probably used to meet up and take a break.
You see a table and chairs tucked away in a cave pocket. It would be easy to escape to take a break once in a while.
You see a lot of supplies strewn about. They're probably being stored here.
You see a gaping hole in the island, and a lot of bird nests nearby.
You find yourself in an enclosed, dead forest. You wonder how the trees grew inside a cave.
You see here what appears to be the saddest bucket in existence. Not a single drop of water landed in it.
You see here an isolated cave area. It's hard to tell what might be in it from the outside.
You find a small offshoot of the island that has not quite collapsed, but looks like it might. The flowers grow nicely here.
You open the door and enter a dimly-lit room with a gaping hole in the floor.
